== Prepare Ingredients ==

Bring a #medium pot{} of plain water to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer 
and cover. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry 
produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces. Core and dice 
@green bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice 
@scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate 
@ginger{1%thumb}.

== Cook Noodles ==

Once large pot of salted water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{4.5%ounce}. 
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Drain and rinse noodles under cold water. Toss with a drizzle of oil. 
Transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pot.

== Sauté Vegetables ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in pot used for noodles over 
medium-high heat. Add sweet potatoes; lightly season with @salt{}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until sweet potatoes begin to soften and brown, 
~{5-6%minutes}.

> If sweet potatoes begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium, adding 
> another drizzle of oil if needed.

Stir in bell pepper, scallion whites, and ginger; cook, stirring occasionally, 
until bell pepper begins to soften, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

== Make Broth ==

To pot with veggies, add 3 cups water, @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, 
@miso sauce concentrate{1}, @pho stock concentrate{1}, and 
@mushroom stock concentrate{1}. Stir to combine. Bring to a boil and cook until 
sweet potatoes are tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @rice wine vinegar{1%tbsp} and cover to keep warm.

== Poach Eggs ==

Once medium pot of plain water is gently simmering, place a #fine-mesh strainer{} 
over a second medium bowl. Coat inside of a #ladle{} with 
@nonstick cooking spray{}.

Working with one @eggs{2} at a time, carefully crack into strainer and 
gently swirl egg for no more than ~{10%seconds}, allowing some of the thinner 
egg white to drain into bowl (the thicker egg white should remain attached).

> Don't let each egg drain for too long!

Carefully tilt strainer with egg toward prepared ladle so that egg slides into 
ladle.

Keeping ladle with egg upright, slowly submerge ladle into medium pot with 
gently simmering plain water, allowing water to gently flow into ladle and 
over egg. Hold in place for ~{5%seconds}, then tip egg into water.

Cook until egg white is set and yolk is cooked to desired doneness, 
~{3-4%minutes}.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, carefully transfer poached egg to a #paper-towel-lined 
plate{}.

Repeat to prep and poach remaining egg. (Discard strained egg whites.)

== Serve ==

Divide noodles between #bowls{} and ladle broth over noodles. Drizzle with 
remaining vinegar to taste.

> A bit more vinegar will help balance out any extra sweetness in the ramen.

Top ramen with poached eggs; sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} and 
@crispy fried onions{1}. Drizzle with @sriracha{1%tsp} to taste. Garnish with 
scallion greens and serve.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or 
> undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.